Use the standard library

This is how to move_one_ball of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   When n is at least 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when

   Remember that drops is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that a is item i in arr
      Remember that b is item (sum of i and 1) in arr
      When a is more than b, then:
         Increase drops
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   When item (diff of n and 1) in arr is more than item 0 in arr, then:
      Increase drops
   End when

   When drops is at least 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   But, if not:
      The answer is 0
   End when
Now you know

>>> move_one_ball of [3, 4, 5, 1, 2]
1
>>> move_one_ball of [3, 5, 4, 1, 2]
0
>>> move_one_ball of [3, 4, 5, 1, 2]
1